HEADWORD: Eleuthero-petalous
<hw>E*leu`ther*o-pet"al*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'eleu`qeros</grk> free + E. <ets>petal</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having the petals free, that is, entirely
separate from each other; -- said of both plant and flower.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

